stateDiagram-v2
    %% decisions: Trace logging lifecycle spans harness_start → task completion.
    %% Idle state = no trace file. Initialized = header written. Recording = events appended.
    %% PhaseComplete = phase-exit recorded. SizeExceeded = 10MB limit hit, skip appends.
    %% Finalized = task done, log sealed. Recording loops on DoD FAIL (retry).
    %% SizeExceeded can transition to PhaseComplete when phase-exit occurs.
    %% Each transition name matches harness action (initTraceFile, appendTrace, phase-enter, phase-exit).
    %% States and transitions cover nominal flow, error recovery (DoD FAIL), size limits, completion.

    Idle --> Initialized: harness_start (initTraceFile)

    Initialized --> Recording: phase-enter event

    Recording --> Recording: appendTrace (tool-access event)
    Recording --> Recording: appendTrace (delegation event)
    Recording --> Recording: appendTrace (context-size event)
    Recording --> Recording: DoD FAIL + retry

    Recording --> PhaseComplete: phase-exit event (DoD PASS)
    Recording --> SizeExceeded: fileSize > 10MB limit

    PhaseComplete --> Recording: next phase-enter

    SizeExceeded --> SizeExceeded: appendTrace skipped (stderr warning)
    SizeExceeded --> PhaseComplete: phase-exit event (DoD PASS)

    PhaseComplete --> Finalized: task completed
